      <bioghist id="aspace_e51a6e8092f1ee3f8896639137855f8f">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>The New Haven Machine Tool Exhibition, the New Haven branch of the American Society of Mechanical Engineers, was incorporated in 1925. Its goal was to promote the scientific development of machine tools and to educate the public by providing practical working demonstrations at exhibitions co-sponsored by the Department of Mechanical Engineering of Yale University and the New Haven Chamber of Commerce. The corporation was dissolved in 1931.</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_ada72ec768aca0043d54aa5519319906">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The records consist of articles of association, incorporation documents, minutes of meetings, administrative files, and printed material, which document the history and activities of New Haven Machine Tool Exhibition.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
